Upstream fixes applied to the bundled iceberg-cpp; the nix package applies
the same patch (see nix/iceberg-cpp/default.nix).

- IcebergThirdpartyToolchain.cmake: the system-Avro discovery looks for an
  `Avro` CMake package, but avro-cpp installs `avro-cpp-config.cmake`.
- arrow_s3_file_io.cc: EnsureS3Initialized() fails (and caches the failure)
  when the host application already initialized Arrow's S3 subsystem, which
  Tenzir's s3 plugin always does; treat that as already-initialized.
- partition_summary.cc: PartitionSummary::Update casts every partition value
  to the partition field type, but LiteralCaster::CastTo refuses null
  literals, so any data file with a null partition value fails to commit.
  The stats themselves handle null fine (contains_null); feed it directly.
- url_encoder.cc: uses uint8_t without including <cstdint>.

diff --git a/cmake_modules/IcebergThirdpartyToolchain.cmake b/cmake_modules/IcebergThirdpartyToolchain.cmake
index 33a1ee4..fd51a0b 100644
--- a/cmake_modules/IcebergThirdpartyToolchain.cmake
+++ b/cmake_modules/IcebergThirdpartyToolchain.cmake
@@ -320,4 +320,4 @@ macro(build_avro)
   else()
     set(AVRO_VENDORED FALSE)
-    list(APPEND ICEBERG_SYSTEM_DEPENDENCIES Avro)
+    list(APPEND ICEBERG_SYSTEM_DEPENDENCIES avro-cpp)
   endif()
